			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Empirical Language Analysis in Software Linguistics</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JeanMarieFavre.html">Jean-Marie Favre</a>, <a href="../profile/DraganGašević.html">Dragan Gašević</a>, <a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a>, <a href="../profile/EkaterinaPek.html">Ekaterina Pek</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_21">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_21</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagM">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> The work is positioned around empirical methods for analyzing languages and their usage as data.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It treats language artifacts/utterances as objects of analysis in “software linguistics”.
</li></ul></li></ul>
